com.hp.opencall.jmsc.test
Class SipPhoneEmulator

java.lang.Object
  com.hp.opencall.jmsc.test.SipPhoneEmulator

public class SipPhoneEmulator
extends java.lang.Object

This object replaces a telephone (SipPhone) in the testing.
It has two ends:

  • one is a NetworkConnection representing the phone call
  • the other is a MediaGroup:
    • playing on this Mediagroup is equivalent to the caller speaking
    • recording on this MediaGroup tells what the caller has said
                        ________________________________________________________________
 implementation:       | myMG <-------join------> ncs[0] <--rtp bridge -------> ncs[1]  |  joinable
                       |                         shadowNC                   myJoinPoint |
                       |________________________________________________________________|
                                                                            
 interface:          play  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - ->>
                   record <- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<<
           receiveSignals <- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -<<
 
 MediaObjects  MG-SipPhoneEmulator-Paul     ShadowNC-SipPhoneEmulator-Paul       Paul
 
 For an mscml implementation:
 
 SIP calls                                            |                            |
                                                      V                            V
                                                      
 media server                                  sip:ivr@mediaserver.com    [depending on join point]
